        <body>
      		
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>July 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5609</date>.</p>
			<p>Revrnd Sir.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">As I have recd with the last steamer<lb/> from <placeName>Europa</placeName> <sic>annother</sic> handsome Sephar Tora<lb/> I take the liberty to inform you of it&#44; and to<lb/> give you an accurate description of the same<lb/> with the polity request to honor me with your<lb/> kind answer&#44; if it would answer your purpose&#63;<lb/> The Sephar is mounted 24 inches and in Pargament<lb/> over 18 inches long&#44; written in handsome large<lb/> letters&#44; mostly new&#44; very well kept&#44; and I have a<lb/> certificate about the correctness. The mounting<lb/> on it is very handsome&#44; and is for the price<lb/> of Eighty Dollars cheap.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I would be glad if I could please you this<lb/> time with the article.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Wishing that this may reach you enjoying<lb/> the divine blessings of health I remain.</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><add>&#63;</add></p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">Most Respectfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)">your</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">most obt Servt</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">L Joalhimfsen<add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
			<p>P.S.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Should you be willing to buy the Sephar&#44; than I could take<lb/> 1 set <add>Hebrew</add> &#38; 1 set <add>&#63;</add>&#44; your edition with in payment</p>
          
        </body>
